&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Product Manager– LAC (Brazil) - 12 months contractor&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Working with governments, foundations, and public sector partners to turn complex challenges into buildable solutions and real impact through product-driven delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Delivery Associates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Delivery Associates (DA) is a global social impact consultancy specializing in transforming the public sector. With over a decade of experience and a foundation in Deliverology®, DA guides leaders through every phase of implementation—delivery-oriented strategy formulation, execution, and evaluation. DA partners with governments, philanthropies, and international organizations, employing actionable strategies to achieve sustainable, lasting outcomes. In every one of our services, you will find a throughline back to this focus on helping our partners deliver better results through better implementation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We work with leaders in the public sector (government, philanthropy, non-profits) to turn ambitious goals into real-world results. Increasingly, this means not only advising on what should be done, but defining, building, and deploying solutions that make change possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an AI Product Manager, you will sit at the intersection of client insight, product thinking, and delivery execution. You will translate complex, often ambiguous government priorities into clear, buildable products, and work alongside software engineers and consulting teams to ensure those solutions are delivered and adopted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a contractor role embedded within small, high-performing delivery teams, where product ownership and execution are tightly integrated. In this role, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Translate delivery needs into buildable products&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Turn project priorities into clear, structured Product Request Documents (PRDs)&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Convert PRDs into precise technical specifications that engineers can execute without ambiguity&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Ensure what is being built is scoped, prioritized, and feasible within delivery timelines&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Identify and resolve risks early, including scope gaps, data limitations, and delivery blockers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work closely with consulting and engineering teams&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Partner with consulting teams to understand delivery goals and translate them into product requirements&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Align engineers and consultants around a shared understanding of what is being built and why&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Act as the bridge between delivery teams and technical execution without duplicating roles&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Support teams in structuring problems and making product-driven decisions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own delivery and execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Own the product lifecycle from scoping through deployment within live engagements&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Coordinate across consulting teams, engineers, and leadership to maintain momentum&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Manage timelines, priorities, and trade-offs to ensure consistent progress&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Define clear success criteria and ensure delivery leads to measurable outcomes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive clarity and accountability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Bring structure to complex, fast-moving projects&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Communicate decisions, trade-offs, and progress clearly across teams&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Maintain focus on outcomes over process&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Operate with autonomy and accountability in high-stakes delivery environments&lt;/p&gt;
